text: I have an elementary school memory of me and my best friend randomly meeting a pair of two boys who looked like an evil version of ourselves, me pointing the similarity out to him, and him appearing to know who they are being weirdly offended like "don't compare me to that type".

This was in our schoolyard so they must have went to our school but I never saw them before or after that day. My friend has zero memory of this and also can't remember who they could have been or why he was so upsset at me pointing out he looks similarly to the other guy. Weird.

They were like an alternative reality creepypasta version of ourselves. My friend was a husky fat kid who played sports outside all day and biked all over town and the Doppelgaenger was more Eric Cartman, sort of cruel looking and mocking. I don't recall any details about my own.

I remember a Jewish friend talked about God's hiddenness itself being hidden, i.e. God hides where one is never able to suspect God to hide. Maybe the more one searches for hidden divinity the more it eludes him so and once he surrenders so it too flows powerfully back into life.

I think a lot of the most tiresome intellectual trends one sees on this site are a direct result of Adderall. It seems to cause a particular type of idiocy where thoughts "skip" from one to another w/o sound logical connections. Like damaged cuneiform tablets with missing words.

Marijuana and THC dull the person down in a very obvious, explicit way, but Adderall users have a distinctive prose with skips and "leaps" that appears sharp, but is like the then-brilliant scribbles one writes down waking after a heavy dream and finds worthless later in the day.

An equivalent would be bodybuilding physiques produced using abuse of HGH/insulin having this grotesque look. I've said it before but I think staying away from Adderall is the number one thing for anyone hoping to make any intellectual contribution or produce any writing of value

Goethe wrote: "The stream is friendly to the miller whom it serves; it likes to pour over the mill wheels; what is the good of it stealing through the valley in apathy?" Dr. Gilbert Ling 凌寧 said carbon dioxide "makes water alive". Our exhalations vitalize nature.

The relation between man and earth is inherent: either Adam tends to the garden or the ground follows in his curse to produce thorns. One cannot renounce his relationship to nature. You sin and fruit no longer offers itself to you. You spill blood and are cursed from the ground.
